        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-04-23T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-04-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="1047" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1047">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.48/4–1247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-04-23T19:00:00-05:00">April 23, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>479. You are authorized to reply to Chinese request for post UNRRA relief along
                    lines para 3 Ur 798 Apr 12 but should include a note of caution stating that
                    once Congress has provided authorization final determination will depend upon
                    ability of Chinese Govt to justify US aid. Emb should undertake exploratory
                    talks re tentative conditions and justifications of needs keeping Dept advised
                    of developments Reur 777 Apr 10. Sent Nanking as Depts 479 repeated Shanghai as
                    Depts 662.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
